The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Britannia profit drops 52%

 Mumbai, Oct. 28 (PTI): Britannia Industries today posted a 51.59 per cent decline in net profit at Rs 21.2 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 43.8 crore in the same quarter last year. Total income (net of excise) increased 22.67 per cent to Rs 552.4 crore for the quarter from Rs 450.3 crore a year ago, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The banks board has appointed Stephan Gerlich as a director at its meeting today. 

 Torrent Pharma 

 Torrent Pharmaceuticals net profit rose 13.45 per cent to Rs 25.64 crore for the quarter ended September 30 from Rs 22.60 crore a year ago. Total income (net of excise) increased 28.30 per cent to Rs 230.16 crore for the quarter from Rs 179.38 crore a year ago, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Nirma net dips

 Nirma Ltd has posted a 54.95 per cent lower net profit at Rs 44.68 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 99.20 crore in the same quarter last fiscal. 




